Tested & proven to be Highly Effective Yet Gentle

The blotting paper test for sunscreen denotes the level of oiliness or greasiness present in the sunscreen when applied to the skin. It helps assess how well the sunscreen formula absorbs into the skin and whether it leaves behind an oily residue. A significant amount of oil on the blotting paper indicates that the sunscreen may be too heavy or greasy for the individual's skin type, potentially leading to discomfort or shine throughout the day. Conversely, minimal oil on the blotting paper suggests that the sunscreen is lightweight and suitable for those who prefer a matte finish

Here is our lightweight broad-spectrum Gel sunscreen which is water resistant, leaves no white cast & has a high SPF 55+ and PA+++ rating to provide the necessary sun protection. 

Apart from the sun filters, it is filled with hydrating agents such as phospholipids & glycerin to provide the necessary hydration to the skin without making it look greasy.
